Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Reframe portfolio for AwardSpring Product Designer role
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Hero: eyebrow → "Product Designer · Ships in Code", headline and sub updated
  to emphasize agentic tooling and production shipping over research-only framing
- Stats: "UX Projects" → "Products Shipped"
- About: heading and body copy rewritten to lead with shipping/building; explicitly
  calls out Claude Code and agentic dev; repositions the researcher identity as
  one dimension, not the whole story
- Skills: reordered to lead with Claude Code, HTML/CSS/JS, Flutter/Firebase
  (technical first, soft skills follow)
- LightDose: description rewritten to make clear it shipped to production,
  not just a Figma handoff
- UXPlore: surfaced the actual research findings (4/10 distrust stat, 3-tab →
  unified search decision) that were buried in the PDF
- Fix broken HTML: removed stray </div> that put project-visual outside the
  featured card's two-column grid
- Mobile: stats strip now visible on <900px as a 4-column row instead of hidden

